    stem: "A 3-year-old girl is brought to your GP clinic by her mother for a routine visit. During examination, you notice multiple bruises in various stages of healing on her back, buttocks, and upper thighs. There is also a patterned bruise on her left cheek that appears to be shaped like a hand. The mother explains she is 'very clumsy' and falls often. The child is quiet and avoids eye contact. What is the most appropriate next step?",
